# Kevin Van Le Portfolio — Design System

## Identity
- Brand: **Kevin Van Le** must be the strongest signal in the first viewport.
- Positioning: ML engineer / researcher — NLP, code models, RL, applied AI systems.
- Site: Jekyll on GitHub Pages (`meloneneis.github.io`). Prefer progressive enhancement over heavy frameworks.

## Visual direction (anti AI-slop)
Do **not** use: purple/indigo gradients, Inter/Roboto/Arial, warm cream+#terracotta serif combo, broadsheet hairline newspaper layouts, neon cyan+violet “neural” kits, glassmorphism card grids, floating badge overlays on heroes, emoji decoration.

### Tokens
- Ink: `#121820`
- Paper: `#eef1f4` (cool stone, not warm cream)
- Deep stage (hero/3D): `#0a1628`
- Accent: `#0d5c63` (deep teal)
- Signal: `#c45c26` (oxide, sparingly — CTAs, highlights)
- Mono labels: IBM Plex Mono; display: Newsreader; UI: Source Sans 3

### Layout
- Hero: full-bleed 3D as background; brand + one headline + one sentence + one CTA group only.
- No cards in hero. Cards only when interaction needs a container.
- Asymmetric work layouts preferred over equal 3-column card grids.
- One job per section.

### Motion
- Prefer purposeful motion: 3D parallax, scroll reveals, blog figure entrance.
- Always respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Content truthfulness
- Only claim projects, results, and credentials backed by Kevin’s repos, thesis, or writing.
- Known anchors: German code search thesis + HF `graphcodebert-base-german`, SemanticPlausibility/SHROOM, DQN racing, CV Agent, glm_ocr, ESMFold blog.
- Do not invent employers, degrees, or metrics.
